<hl>
<seg id=1> The World Bank to loan Palestine 0.25 billion US dollar as aid </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Jerusalem, August 31, (Xinhua News Agency) The "Jerusalem Post" reported that, Saval the now visiting Director General of the General Office of Israel Foreign Ministry in the US said that the World Bank had decided to provide the Palestinian authority with 0.25 billion dollars of loan as aid by the end of 1994. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> This decision broke the stalemate between the loan lenders and the Palestinian authority lasting for a year. </seg>
<seg id=4> At the meeting aiding Palestinian autonomy in Washington on Oct. 1 last year, the aiding countries promised to provide 2.4 billion dollars of development aid in 5 years, with 0.75 billion appropriated in the first year. </seg>
<seg id=5> Yet the aiding countries said that, the autonomous regions of Palestine lacked necessary mechanism and account to deal with the loans, so they refuse to completely fulfill their promise. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Saval also said that, though the US and the World Bank were not fully satisfied with the accountant work of Palestine, they still agreed to pay part of the money. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The Palestinian leader Arafat and other Palestinian officials always criticized that the aiding countries failed to fulfill their promise to provide the aid completely and on time. </seg>
<seg id=8> It was expected that the chief Palestinian negotiator Shaars and the Israel chief Negotiator Rosechield would negotiate with the US and the World bank upon the fulfill of the aid loans. </seg>
</p>
